Track and Trace
=================

Track and Trace data consists of Consignment Status, Proof of Delivery (PODs) and Scan Events. Track and Trace data API is POST request and each of track and trace data can be fetched using different API endpoints. AccessToken from authentication step is passed as header parameter in the request.


Consignment Status
---------------------------------------
Consignment Status API sends back Track and Trace status of a given Job Number. Consignment Status endpoint is given below::

    POST https://api.tmspanel.com.au/api/public/v1/tnt/status

Consignment Status - Example Request
---------------------------------------
Example request is given below::

    curl -POST https://api.tmspanel.com.au/api/public/v1/tnt/status
    -H "Content-type: application/json" 
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $AccessToken" 
    -d '{
    "JobNumber" : "1395"
    }'

Proof of Delivery (POD)
---------------------------------------
These are the types of Proof of Delivery (POD) documents that TMS API provides and are shared for integration. 

* Job POD
* Job Leg POD
* Customer POD (Sender & Receiver)
* Scanned POD
* POD Photos from Mobile application
  
POD documents can be fetched using given Job Number. Proof of Delivery endpoint is given below::

    POST https://api.tmspanel.com.au/api/public/v1/tnt/pods

Proof of Delivery - Example Request
---------------------------------------
Example request is given below::

    curl -POST https://api.tmspanel.com.au/api/public/v1/tnt/pods
    -H "Content-type: application/json" 
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $AccessToken" 
    -d '{
    "JobNumber" : "10510"
    }' 
  
Proof of Delivery - Example Response
---------------------------------------
Example response is given below::

    {
    "Success": true,
    "Error": null,
    "Data": [

Scan Events
---------------------------------------
Scanning events in TMS are at either entire job level or individual items or product level. There are currently the following scan points

* Load Vehicle Scan
* Unload Vehicle Scan
* Pickup Scan
* Delivery Scan
* Scan into Depot
* Scan on to Manifest 

Scan Events endpoint is given below::

    POST https://api.tmspanel.com.au/api/public/v1/tnt/scans

Scan Events - Example Request
---------------------------------------
Example request is given below::

    curl -POST https://api.tmspanel.com.au/api/public/v1/tnt/scans
    -H "Content-type: application/json" 
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $AccessToken" 
    -d '{
    "JobNumber" : "TRNS2198"
    }'
  
Scan Events - Example Response
---------------------------------------
Example response is given below::

    "Error": null,
